00:31:19.030 --> 00:31:27.250
Q So one thing you haven't talked about very
much in your talk so far is religion.

00:31:27.250 --> 00:31:28.679
Michael Specter: Yeah.

00:31:28.679 --> 00:31:37.950
Q Do you think the fact that a lot of people
are indoctrinated from early age to believe

00:31:37.950 --> 00:31:39.490
things that aren't proved or provable affects
their take on things later in life?

00:31:39.490 --> 00:31:40.789
Michael Specter: Yeah. I try to duck the religion
thing as much as possible.

00:31:40.789 --> 00:31:44.899
But I will say this.
I don't think that religion has to be in conflict

00:31:44.899 --> 00:31:47.879
with science.
And there's lots of examples, including Albert

00:31:47.879 --> 00:31:53.379
Einstein, to prove me right.
Yeah, there are fundamentalists -- Christians,

00:31:53.379 --> 00:31:57.850
Jews, Muslims -- tons of people who are never
going to accept reality.

00:31:57.850 --> 00:32:03.390
But most people are not like that.
And I don't see why a religion -- if people

00:32:03.390 --> 00:32:08.460
feel good about religion and it gives them
some peace, I don't see why that has to interfere

00:32:08.460 --> 00:32:13.870
with the scientific method and talking about
repeating studies, showing how they work,

00:32:13.870 --> 00:32:17.519
showing what they do, and showing what happens
when you don't do them.

00:32:17.519 --> 00:32:22.499
I may be utopian, but I don't think that is
the fundamental problem.

00:32:22.499 --> 00:32:23.499
But it is something to think about.

00:32:23.499 --> 00:32:37.350
Q So my knowledge of history is not that great,
but my impression is So Europe sort of went

00:32:37.350 --> 00:32:53.590
through a transition a couple of hundred years
of sort of superstition to having a method.

00:32:53.590 --> 00:33:02.059
Since then, a lot of other countries have
made that transition or are in

00:33:02.059 --> 00:33:03.059
the process of transition.
Have you researched at all, How does that

00:33:03.059 --> 00:33:04.059
transition happen?
You know, what's -- we have different cases,

00:33:04.059 --> 00:33:05.059
because it happens in different kinds of places,
like different here than there?

00:33:05.059 --> 00:33:09.409
Michael Specter: Well, it's a good question.
I think some of it is just level of education

00:33:09.409 --> 00:33:13.749
and the number of people and the percentage
of people who are educated at a certain level.

00:33:13.749 --> 00:33:17.049
But I would say this about Europe.
Yeah, they went through a transition a couple

00:33:17.049 --> 00:33:19.519
hundred years ago.
I think they might be going through another

00:33:19.519 --> 00:33:23.139
transition right now.
Because you say the word 'genetically modified

00:33:23.139 --> 00:33:27.029
food' in that part of the world and you better
have a suit of armor.

00:33:27.029 --> 00:33:31.379
And again, there are reasons for that because,
you know, they don't need genetically modified

00:33:31.379 --> 00:33:36.549
corn or tasteless tomatoes, but their opposition
is so profound.

00:33:36.549 --> 00:33:41.450
And the thing that kills me about that is,
So you're an environmentist and what do you

00:33:41.450 --> 00:33:45.059
want?
Less water use? Less insecticide on the land?

00:33:45.059 --> 00:33:48.460
Less energy used to get to crops?
These things can do that.

00:33:48.460 --> 00:33:52.789
And actually the World Wildlife Fund has,
thank God, come out and said, "Gee, maybe

00:33:52.789 --> 00:33:57.649
this biotechnology stuff is okay."
But I see it going in reverse in Europe actually

00:33:57.649 --> 00:34:03.000
more rapidly than it's going in reverse here.
I don't know why they are okay with evolution

00:34:03.000 --> 00:34:08.260
and we're not.
That's over my head -- above my pay rate.

00:34:08.260 --> 00:34:12.760
But on the other stuff I don't think -- I
do see them moving backwards.

00:34:12.760 --> 00:34:18.809
I see a lot of moving backwards.
Well, there may be a pendulum and that may

00:34:18.809 --> 00:34:24.149
seem natural, but all I know is that, you
know, we used to die at the age of 40.

00:34:24.149 --> 00:34:27.089
That was when we died.
It wasn't thousands of years ago.

00:34:27.089 --> 00:34:32.069
It was 125 years ago, or 150 years ago.
And now, we die at the age of 80.

00:34:32.069 --> 00:34:36.569
My grandfather died when he was 62, and that
was about 40 years ago.

00:34:36.569 --> 00:34:40.970
And it was sad, but nobody said, "Oh, my God.
He was only 62," because you were supposed

00:34:40.970 --> 00:34:44.329
to die when you're 62.
Well now, you're supposed to die when you're

00:34:44.329 --> 00:34:49.099
82.
And people say when someone dies at 62, "Gee,

00:34:49.099 --> 00:34:52.929
he got robbed of, you know, a bunch of life."
That's just in one generation.

00:34:52.929 --> 00:34:58.319
That isn't 500 years.
So the advances we've made are just incredible.

00:34:58.319 --> 00:35:03.170
And yet, we seem to be sliding backward in
the way we approach them, and, I think, part

00:35:03.170 --> 00:35:11.730
of it is we take for granted what we have.
But for what it's worth.

00:35:11.730 --> 00:35:14.309
Anything else?
Okay.

00:35:14.309 --> 00:35:21.630
Go forth, plant genetically engineered food,
swear off organics, and thank you very much.

